Ecological notes : very common in broad-leaved and mixed woodland; common in carr woodland; also found on heathland; wetlands including fen, raised bog, sedge beds, water meadows and gravel pits; mossy rocks by waterfall; old hedges; grassland and scrub in old limestone quarry; gardens. Reared from poplar log, borings of the beetle
Hylesinus fraxini
and fungus
Auricularia mesenterica
. iii–xi.
